tyle="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">run its own well-respected accreditation scheme for lawye</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rs for almost 15 years </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and has 1,500 accredited lawyers on its books</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. W</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e fully appreciate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, therefore,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the value and importance of accreditation.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We are committed to offering any assistance we can to the Government on this matter</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and we have already emphas</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ised the crucial importance of clarity in the development of the register.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he clinical definition of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a whiplash injury </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">needs to be very clear as there are some types of injury associated with whiplash which are different from the soft tissue neck and back</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> injuries which most people normally </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">refer to as ‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">whiplash</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It is important to note </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">as well </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that ‘whiplash’ is actually the mechanism by which an injury is sustained rather than the injury itself. A whiplash of the neck may cause ligament and nerve </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">damage, soft tissue injury or even a fracture.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> There are often ancillary injuries.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> If the Government is seeking to accredit medical specialists it needs to be clear w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">hat those specialists will be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">required to deal with</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. There appear to be several options av</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ailable</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">road traffic claims where the only